 B dropped 5% to $21.67. ...
Market pros have been critical of PennyMac's actions, which differed from t=
he vast majority of payers of floating-rate instruments that transitioned t=
o SOFR from Libor. "PMT's behavior was particularly nasty, even exploitativ=
e, to investors," wrote Charles Lieberman, chief investment officer of Advi=
sors Capital Management, in an email. He's also an investor in other mortga=
