I don=E2=80=99t know! The thing is, PennyMac
  [2]
=C2=A0can=E2=80=99t just change the terms of its preferred stocks by itself=
. Either the Libor Act changed those terms (in which case PennyMac=E2=80=99=
s shares pay SOFR, plus=C2=A00.26161%, plus 5.831% or 5.99%), or it didn=E2=
=80=99t (in which case they pay 8.125% or 8% flat). Apparently PennyMac tak=
es the view that the third option in its preferred stock =E2=80=94=C2=A0the=
 rate stays fixed forever =E2=80=94=C2=A0is a fallback provision, and so th=
e Libor Act didn=E2=80=99t override it, so that=E2=80=99s what the preferre=
d stock now pays. (Here is  the press release, and here is the original 201=
7 prospectus for the 8.125% preferred.) That strikes me as =E2=80=A6 probab=
ly=C2=A0correct? The contract says that, if Libor goes away, the rate stays=
 fixed forever. Libor went away, so the rate stays fixed forever.
Casual examination of other fixed-to-floating preferreds=C2=A0suggests that=
 PennyMac is not alone. A lot of banks did replace all their Libors with SO=
FRs along the lines of the Libor Act; here are announcements from  Morgan S=
tanley,  Citizens Financial Group Inc.=C2=A0and=C2=A0Regions Financial Corp=
.=C2=A0But here is a more complicated  announcement from State Street Corp.=
=C2=A0from June. State Street has some fixed-to-floating preferred stock (a=
nd bonds) that were indexed to Libor, and that will now, under the Libor Ac=
t,=C2=A0be indexed to SOFR. But it also has some that won=E2=80=99t be:
Each series of State Street=E2=80=99s Preferred Stock listed in Annex 3 to =
this press release is governed by the terms of a certificate of designation=
 (each, a =E2=80=9CCertificate=E2=80=9D) and will not transition to Three-m=
onth CME Term SOFR by operation of law or otherwise. The Certificate for ea=
ch such series specifies a fixed dividend rate (the =E2=80=9CDividend Rate=
=E2=80=9D) for a dividend period beginning on a specified date (the =E2=80=
=9CCommencement Date=E2=80=9D), in each case as shown for each series in An=
nex 3 to this press release, if Three-Month USD LIBOR cannot otherwise be d=
etermined as provided in the applicable Certificate. Given that the Commenc=
ement Date for each such series follows the LIBOR Replacement Date, the Div=
idend Rate for each series after the applicable Commencement Date will be t=
he applicable fixed rate specified in Annex 3 to this press release.
That is, some of State Street=E2=80=99s preferreds are in the same boat as =
PennyMac=E2=80=99s: They=C2=A0currently=C2=A0have a fixed rate (=E2=80=9Cth=
e Commencement Date for each such series follows the LIBOR Replacement Date=
=E2=80=9D), so their current interest rate doesn=E2=80=99t change due to th=
e Libor Act. And when they=C2=A0move=C2=A0to a floating rate in the future,=
 there is fallback language saying that, if there=E2=80=99s no Libor, they =
