in ETFs replace futures-based Bitcoin ETFs,=E2=80=9D wrote JPMorgan strateg=
ist Nikolaos Panigirtzoglou in a July note.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I hesitate to say this, but when I think about=
 derivatives-based ETFs outside of crypto, I tend to think of three main us=
e cases:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Commodity ETFs are often futures-base=
